==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Coccus
<hw>Coc"cus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Cocci</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/ grain, seed.
See <er>Cochineal</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>One of
the separable carpels of a dry fruit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of hemipterous insects,
including scale insects, and the cochineal insect (<spn>Coccus
cacti</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>A form of bacteria, shaped like a
globule.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Coccygeal</ent>⟦br⟧
